1
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:06,264
(Yume) Um...

2
00:00:06,264 --> 00:00:09,561
The beer is freezing cold

3
00:00:11,297 --> 00:00:16,297
Ah... then do you want a photo?

4
00:00:16,297 --> 00:00:19,099
Huh? During the day, that... the one I took with that one.

5
00:00:19,099 --> 00:00:23,033
I only took pictures of mine...

6
00:00:23,033 --> 00:00:25,363
(Misato) Free?

7
00:00:25,363 --> 00:00:27,363
Huh?

8
00:00:28,792 --> 00:00:32,099
Ah...of course

9
00:00:32,099 --> 00:00:38,132
So, um... would you like to come over here for a little while?

10
00:00:42,660 --> 00:00:46,132
It's definitely different...

11
00:00:48,429 --> 00:00:52,924
I don't know... I don't know anymore...

12
00:00:52,924 --> 00:00:57,528
Um... can I ask you to talk to me for a moment?

13
00:01:02,099 --> 00:01:06,033
I don't like something about myself

14
00:01:07,330 --> 00:01:10,066
I mean, it irritates people...

15
00:01:10,066 --> 00:01:15,594
In my life, I am always doing important things wrong at important times.

16
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:22,396
I can't forgive myself for being like that.

17
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:30,462
for me…

18
00:01:30,462 --> 00:01:33,330
Could you please stay a little longer?

19
00:01:56,495 --> 00:01:59,957
(Misato) What is it that you can't forgive so much?

20
00:01:59,957 --> 00:02:04,396
Huh? (Misato) About myself

21
00:02:04,396 --> 00:02:10,264
I don't like it because I make so many mistakes

22
00:02:14,726 --> 00:02:17,165
At the ramen shop at work...

23
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,858
When I throw away the juice that smells like muddy water

24
00:02:21,858 --> 00:02:26,264
That's a 58 year old sauce.

25
00:02:26,264 --> 00:02:32,198
And many other things...I've been fired many times already.

26
00:02:32,198 --> 00:02:37,363
Eh, but...

27
00:02:37,363 --> 00:02:41,099
If it was that much of a mistake

28
00:02:41,099 --> 00:02:44,165
That's within the permissible range, right?

29
00:02:48,198 --> 00:02:50,891
Actually when I was a child...

30
00:02:53,759 --> 00:02:55,462
(Misato) Huh?

31
00:03:01,594 --> 00:03:05,132
Maybe I can try to forgive

32
00:03:08,495 --> 00:03:10,165
I wonder...

33
00:03:11,429 --> 00:03:16,627
(Misato) Because you gave me beer.

34
00:03:16,627 --> 00:03:18,297
Huh?

35
00:03:21,066 --> 00:03:22,858
(sigh)

36
00:03:22,858 --> 00:03:29,099
Even if I make a lot of mistakes, I'm not a bad person.

37
00:03:34,495 --> 00:03:37,132
me too…

38
00:03:39,891 --> 00:03:44,066
Maybe I should try to forgive you

39
00:03:44,066 --> 00:03:46,792
Huh?

40
00:03:46,792 --> 00:03:52,000
My kind of...

41
00:03:55,330 --> 00:03:58,000
Where I made a mistake

42
00:04:02,264 --> 00:04:04,000
(sound of opening a can)

43
00:04:18,462 --> 00:04:20,132
(sound of drinking beer)

44
00:04:21,726 --> 00:04:23,726
good

45
00:04:27,462 --> 00:04:29,132
Are you going home?

46
00:04:30,726 --> 00:04:33,660
(Klaxon)

47
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:46,594
good morning

48
00:04:51,330 --> 00:04:54,495
good morning

49
00:04:54,495 --> 00:04:57,132
(Mio) Why are you... Ah! it hurts…

50
00:04:57,132 --> 00:05:02,858
Why is it better not to move?

51
00:05:02,858 --> 00:05:06,033
Don't you remember?

52
00:05:06,033 --> 00:05:11,660
I remember, but...

53
00:05:13,396 --> 00:05:16,495
What do you mean "good morning"? I'm not angry.

54
00:05:16,495 --> 00:05:18,429
(Yume/Mio) Huh?

55
00:05:18,429 --> 00:05:22,528
Ouch... I don't say "good morning" in such a stupid way!

56
00:05:22,528 --> 00:05:24,198
What do you mean "I'm not angry"? it was yesterday

57
00:05:24,198 --> 00:05:26,000
Mio-chan suddenly... "suddenly"?

58
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:28,264
Huh? What do you mean suddenly?

59
00:05:28,264 --> 00:05:31,957
You say something suddenly, suddenly, without any cause or effect.

60
00:05:31,957 --> 00:05:34,924
Suddenly, BOOM! Ah... that wasn't sudden.

61
00:05:34,924 --> 00:05:37,033
How many months has it been? With a face like that dog

62
00:05:37,033 --> 00:05:40,561
What you did and the lies you told

63
00:05:40,561 --> 00:05:42,495
The dust piled up and became a mountain! What is it?

64
00:05:42,495 --> 00:05:45,528
I know! I know, but...

65
00:05:45,528 --> 00:05:49,231
I understand, so don't say you're not angry.

66
00:05:49,231 --> 00:05:50,891
And you pulled it in the end, right?

67
00:05:50,891 --> 00:05:52,561
I'm not pulling it!

68
00:05:52,561 --> 00:05:54,495
I'm here because you pulled me, right?

69
00:05:54,495 --> 00:05:57,726
I pulled it, but...

70
00:05:57,726 --> 00:05:59,891
But I had no choice but to come out.

71
00:05:59,891 --> 00:06:02,825
It's not out. What does "out" mean?

72
00:06:02,825 --> 00:06:05,561
You were helpless

73
00:06:05,561 --> 00:06:07,891
"I feel sorry for you, I can't help it.

74
00:06:07,891 --> 00:06:09,792
Yume-chan, that's how I lived my life.

75
00:06:09,792 --> 00:06:11,462
That's why I said "good morning"

76
00:06:11,462 --> 00:06:13,132
Huh? (knock)

77
00:06:13,132 --> 00:06:15,825
(Nurse) Good morning, do you have any pain?

78
00:06:15,825 --> 00:06:19,198
Um, I'm sorry, I can't. If you still move like that.

79
00:06:19,198 --> 00:06:22,495
We were both lucky and escaped with only minor injuries.

80
00:06:22,495 --> 00:06:24,396
I'm sorry it's taking a long time to heal.

81
00:06:24,396 --> 00:06:26,297
Can I have a separate room with this person?

82
00:06:26,297 --> 00:06:27,957
(Nurse) Huh? No, it's already

83
00:06:27,957 --> 00:06:30,825
It's fine if it's small, like that bench in the hallway...

84
00:06:30,825 --> 00:06:32,660
(Nurse) Sorry, I'm busy right now.

85
00:06:32,660 --> 00:06:34,660
I don't mind if I go outside (Nurse) Huh?

86
00:06:34,660 --> 00:06:37,165
It doesn't matter if it's a toilet, a storage room, etc.

87
00:06:37,165 --> 00:06:38,825
(Nurse) They're not children.

88
00:06:38,825 --> 00:06:42,198
I can be discharged from the hospital tomorrow, so no, no, no, no!

89
00:06:42,198 --> 00:06:45,594
I can't stay with you all day, so I'm fine with using the toilet.

90
00:06:45,594 --> 00:06:49,033
Please wait a moment

91
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:51,363
please

92
00:07:07,693 --> 00:07:09,363
(Endo) What happened?

93
00:07:09,363 --> 00:07:11,132
Can you tell me more about the situation at that time?

94
00:07:11,132 --> 00:07:13,891
I pressed it (Endo) Huh?

95
00:07:13,891 --> 00:07:16,891
I tried to push her down the stairs.

96
00:07:16,891 --> 00:07:19,231
Is that true? Huh?

97
00:07:19,231 --> 00:07:21,231
So what? Am I being arrested?

98
00:07:21,231 --> 00:07:24,528
She supported her mother and was not charged with any crime.

99
00:07:24,528 --> 00:07:27,165
No one said that, right?

100
00:07:27,165 --> 00:07:29,330
Huh? You...

101
00:07:29,330 --> 00:07:33,000
(Endo) Please calm down! I will ask you for details personally.

102
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,462
I mean, why are you here? (Sakuma) Huh?

103
00:07:35,462 --> 00:07:38,429
(Endo) Well... Mr. Sakuma... I can't leave him alone after all.

104
00:07:38,429 --> 00:07:40,462
Huh? With Taro

105
00:07:40,462 --> 00:07:45,198
I feel like I need to talk to you properly, so I'm worried...

106
00:07:45,198 --> 00:07:46,957
I went there with Mr. Osako, but he wasn't there...

107
00:07:46,957 --> 00:07:51,693
How many times have I come home? I have a bad feeling...

108
00:07:51,693 --> 00:07:55,660
I contacted Mr. Endo to see if something strange was going on...

109
00:07:55,660 --> 00:07:57,330
So why did you come?

110
00:07:57,330 --> 00:08:01,957
It's partly my fault that the two of us turned out like this...

111
00:08:01,957 --> 00:08:06,891
No, I know, but I shouldn't say things like this now.

112
00:08:06,891 --> 00:08:08,825
But I also wanted to do the right thing just once...

113
00:08:08,825 --> 00:08:11,594
Are you saying that's a mistake? (Endo) Anyway

114
00:08:11,594 --> 00:08:14,099
I'll talk to you privately, so it's not her fault.

115
00:08:14,099 --> 00:08:16,099
(Endo) Huh?

116
00:08:17,330 --> 00:08:21,198
all…

117
00:08:21,198 --> 00:08:25,462
It's really all my fault

118
00:08:25,462 --> 00:08:28,891
(Ambulance siren)

119
00:08:33,264 --> 00:08:35,561
It hurts...

120
00:08:41,462 --> 00:08:43,528
It hurts...

121
00:08:43,528 --> 00:08:45,759
it hurts…

122
00:09:02,099 --> 00:09:06,264
Sigh... just a moment...

123
00:09:21,165 --> 00:09:24,528
Why did you help me?

124
00:09:26,231 --> 00:09:29,132
That's... right away...

125
00:09:29,132 --> 00:09:36,000
The day I first met you, not your mom, but me.

126
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:39,000
That too...

127
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:42,891
After that? Huh?

128
00:09:42,891 --> 00:09:48,033
Go bungying, eat crab, go to a club, drink alcohol.

129
00:09:48,033 --> 00:09:51,825
Why did you act like we were friends?

130
00:09:51,825 --> 00:09:54,825
It's not pretend

131
00:09:56,396 --> 00:09:59,759
I really thought about it

132
00:09:59,759 --> 00:10:05,924
I want to forgive you

133
00:10:05,924 --> 00:10:12,561
But... you were next to me the whole time.

134
00:10:13,561 --> 00:10:19,792
I wonder what that felt like

135
00:10:26,099 --> 00:10:29,099
forever…

136
00:10:42,132 --> 00:10:45,033
sorry…

137
00:10:51,264 --> 00:10:56,627
Did you really know? Huh?

138
00:11:01,264 --> 00:11:05,462
The reason my mother wanted to die

139
00:11:06,528 --> 00:11:10,165
I really don't know that

140
00:11:10,165 --> 00:11:16,462
why? Because we were together in the last moment, right?

141
00:11:16,462 --> 00:11:20,132
We drank beer and talked.

142
00:11:20,132 --> 00:11:23,759
We talked, but...

143
00:11:23,759 --> 00:11:28,462
I feel like my story was heard.

144
00:11:28,462 --> 00:11:33,165
I feel bad for myself because I keep making mistakes...

145
00:11:38,561 --> 00:11:43,330
Did you also talk about your childhood? Huh?

146
00:11:43,330 --> 00:11:47,198
about your father

147
00:11:48,198 --> 00:11:53,165
Oh, by the way, you told another lie, right?

148
00:11:53,165 --> 00:11:58,660
Huh? Name About your mother

149
00:11:58,660 --> 00:12:01,165
I wish your birth was just a dream.

150
00:12:01,165 --> 00:12:08,000
You said that's where the name came from, but what is that? A lie to gain sympathy?

151
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:11,726
That's not really a lie...

152
00:12:11,726 --> 00:12:15,429
Well, whatever is fine.

153
00:12:15,429 --> 00:12:18,429
I'm really sorry

154
00:12:22,528 --> 00:12:25,660
Which part are you apologizing for?

155
00:12:28,528 --> 00:12:30,528
it is…

156
00:12:31,792 --> 00:12:35,660
Everything... Everything I...

157
00:12:35,660 --> 00:12:41,099
"It's all my fault" is an escape, isn't it?

158
00:12:41,099 --> 00:12:43,363
Huh? Because that's it

159
00:12:43,363 --> 00:12:45,330
The other day I was thinking and thinking

160
00:12:45,330 --> 00:12:47,495
That I said I wanted to forgive you

161
00:12:47,495 --> 00:12:49,957
I mean, I haven't heard anything like that at all.

162
00:12:49,957 --> 00:12:53,363
That doesn't mean I'm ignoring you.

163
00:12:53,363 --> 00:12:55,132
For now, let's just say it's all my fault.

164
00:12:55,132 --> 00:12:59,957
Somehow, I felt guilty and felt better.

165
00:12:59,957 --> 00:13:01,627
What are you really angry about?

166
00:13:01,627 --> 00:13:04,165
It doesn't mean I don't think about that at all.

167
00:13:04,165 --> 00:13:06,825
No... no difference

168
00:13:09,165 --> 00:13:12,792
Well, it's okay because it's different now.

169
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:18,297
I don't think that's what you should do as a friend.

170
00:13:20,099 --> 00:13:23,891
You said something like you wanted to make amends.

171
00:13:23,891 --> 00:13:27,297
Simply say that everything is bad and stop thinking.

172
00:13:27,297 --> 00:13:29,957
What was really the biggest mistake?

173
00:13:29,957 --> 00:13:32,495
As long as I'm running away from that kind of thing

174
00:13:32,495 --> 00:13:36,198
I don't think there can be true redemption.

175
00:13:49,066 --> 00:14:03,066
♬〜

176
00:14:03,066 --> 00:14:08,231
(breathing heavily)

177
00:14:09,264 --> 00:14:12,660
(Takeshi)《Quickly...》

178
00:14:12,660 --> 00:14:17,297
《I wish it was all a dream...》

179
00:14:17,297 --> 00:14:20,264
《That you were born》

180
00:14:23,924 --> 00:14:25,924
(conflict sound)

181
00:14:25,924 --> 00:14:33,363
(breathing heavily)

182
00:14:33,363 --> 00:14:37,462
(Nurse) Mr. Nakata? Yume Nakata!

183
00:14:37,462 --> 00:14:41,858
Have you woken up? Huh?

184
00:14:41,858 --> 00:14:46,429
(Nurse) Even if I woke you up, you wouldn't wake up, so I finished eating.

185
00:14:46,429 --> 00:14:48,594
Ah...

186
00:14:50,627 --> 00:14:54,033
(Nurse) Ah, your friend just got discharged from the hospital.

187
00:14:54,033 --> 00:14:55,693
Huh?

188
00:14:55,693 --> 00:14:58,165
Mr. Nakata also had another check-up with the doctor after this.

189
00:14:58,165 --> 00:15:01,660
If there are no problems, you can go home.

190
00:15:01,660 --> 00:15:21,660
♬〜

191
00:15:21,660 --> 00:15:34,165
♬〜

192
00:15:34,165 --> 00:15:36,693
(Taro) Sister!

193
00:15:50,264 --> 00:15:52,627
thank you

194
00:16:06,165 --> 00:16:10,363
Does that look like a dog?

195
00:16:10,363 --> 00:16:13,759
Ah... Yeah, just a little bit.

196
00:16:13,759 --> 00:16:17,396
(Taro) I got a call from Kenken.

197
00:16:20,495 --> 00:16:23,561
When did you come here?

198
00:16:23,561 --> 00:16:27,957
As soon as I got a call from my sister yesterday.

199
00:16:29,594 --> 00:16:33,957
After all, that house was at its limit.

200
00:16:37,033 --> 00:16:40,594
I'm glad you're doing well

201
00:16:50,957 --> 00:16:58,693
Well then... Thank you for the tea.

202
00:17:03,594 --> 00:17:05,759
Good job

203
00:17:07,099 --> 00:17:09,858
(Taro) My sister...

204
00:17:11,396 --> 00:17:14,726
(Taro) I wonder if he's a really bad guy...

205
00:17:14,726 --> 00:17:16,396
Huh?

206
00:17:17,726 --> 00:17:25,165
I thought about everything about this time

207
00:17:25,165 --> 00:17:32,396
What my sister did and what she was lied to about.

208
00:17:32,396 --> 00:17:35,957
I also remember my father.

209
00:17:35,957 --> 00:17:42,132
I wonder if he's seriously a really bad guy.

210
00:17:42,132 --> 00:17:48,495
And the conclusion...

211
00:17:48,495 --> 00:17:56,330
Ah, I just feel like I'm an irredeemable idiot.

212
00:17:56,330 --> 00:17:58,066
Huh?

213
00:17:58,066 --> 00:18:04,132
No, if that's all there is to it, it won't be enough.

214
00:18:04,132 --> 00:18:08,396
It's all about things that can't be undone...

215
00:18:10,099 --> 00:18:13,594
But for me either is fine

216
00:18:16,825 --> 00:18:22,825
Whether you're there or not, it doesn't matter

217
00:18:25,033 --> 00:18:35,429
Something like trauma, family, toxic parents, etc.

218
00:18:35,429 --> 00:18:38,693
I'm a little bored

219
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:50,231
(Taro) I just want to go on to the next one.

220
00:18:53,660 --> 00:18:56,000
I see.

221
00:18:58,825 --> 00:19:04,297
That girl, that girl... Who is Sakura?

222
00:19:04,297 --> 00:19:10,198
It seems like he can't think of kissing, huh?

223
00:19:10,198 --> 00:19:14,660
So are you just friends?

224
00:19:14,660 --> 00:19:18,396
Ah, we became friends.

225
00:19:19,726 --> 00:19:25,561
(Taro) Do you want to eat? Hehe, did you make it? that

226
00:19:25,561 --> 00:19:29,693
But I'm definitely making a mistake somehow, it's so bad

227
00:19:29,693 --> 00:19:32,165
Hehehe

228
00:19:32,165 --> 00:19:35,231
Good job

229
00:19:35,231 --> 00:19:37,561
let's see…

230
00:19:37,561 --> 00:19:48,627
♬〜

231
00:19:48,627 --> 00:19:51,495
Hehehehe

232
00:19:51,495 --> 00:19:55,033
Huh? Hehehehe

233
00:19:55,033 --> 00:19:59,858
That's fucking bad hehehehe

234
00:20:16,198 --> 00:20:20,693
My mom wanted to eat it, haha.

235
00:20:20,693 --> 00:20:26,759
(Chime) Yes! Ah... yes

236
00:20:26,759 --> 00:20:31,330
(cell phone vibration sound)

237
00:20:33,165 --> 00:20:36,033
Oh, Sakura?

238
00:20:36,033 --> 00:20:39,264
I mean... I always feel like I have free time like this.

239
00:20:39,264 --> 00:20:43,297
Even if I get a call, it's a problem...

240
00:20:43,297 --> 00:20:44,957
Huh?

241
00:20:46,660 --> 00:20:48,330
(Taro) Sister...

242
00:20:48,330 --> 00:20:50,000
what?

243
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:28,858
(Sutra reading)

244
00:21:28,858 --> 00:21:33,627
(Shigehiko) Ah, um...

245
00:21:33,627 --> 00:21:36,759
(Sutra reading)

246
00:21:36,759 --> 00:21:39,462
Did Mio-chan call you?

247
00:21:39,462 --> 00:21:44,198
(Sutra reading)

248
00:21:44,198 --> 00:21:47,231
Sorry, I didn't contact you...

249
00:21:47,231 --> 00:21:53,264
(Chihiro) I really just wanted to raise some incense today.

250
00:21:53,264 --> 00:22:05,429
(Sutra reading)

251
00:22:05,429 --> 00:22:07,099
(clicks tongue)

252
00:22:08,957 --> 00:22:11,957
(Sae) Dad, be careful there.

253
00:22:11,957 --> 00:22:20,396
♬〜

254
00:22:20,396 --> 00:22:25,231
Eh, just some incense is fine, right?

255
00:22:25,231 --> 00:22:34,033
♬〜

256
00:22:34,033 --> 00:22:37,132
(Shigehiko) Ah, the sushi here is quite delicious.

257
00:22:37,132 --> 00:22:39,462
Hahahahaha

258
00:22:40,462 --> 00:22:42,759
Excuse me for a moment...

259
00:22:42,759 --> 00:22:46,198
(Shigehiko) I forgot to get the receipt from the sushi restaurant.

260
00:22:47,693 --> 00:22:49,792
That's why I still can't drink alcohol.

261
00:22:49,792 --> 00:22:52,132
The teacher said it was fine too.

262
00:22:52,132 --> 00:22:54,132
Because it's no good

263
00:22:56,330 --> 00:22:58,330
that…

264
00:23:01,429 --> 00:23:03,825
Um... (Sae) What is an insane person?

265
00:23:03,825 --> 00:23:06,594
I don't want you to think that, huh?

266
00:23:06,594 --> 00:23:11,363
But I thought that if I didn't come today, I might be able to escape.

267
00:23:11,363 --> 00:23:17,561
I wanted to settle it, or rather, be satisfied with it in my own way.

268
00:23:18,924 --> 00:23:21,528
You said you wanted to end it all.

269
00:23:21,528 --> 00:23:25,198
If so, at least what are you thinking now?

270
00:23:25,198 --> 00:23:28,297
I wanted to ask you

271
00:23:28,297 --> 00:23:30,561
who is the worst

272
00:23:30,561 --> 00:23:34,033
Who do you think is to blame for this?

273
00:23:34,033 --> 00:23:36,363
I want to hear it from your mouth too

274
00:23:36,363 --> 00:23:42,561
That's why I asked you today. I'm sorry.

275
00:23:42,561 --> 00:23:47,066
But today, I want to see my mother off properly.

276
00:23:47,066 --> 00:23:50,627
(Chihiro) It's my daughter who's at fault.

277
00:23:50,627 --> 00:23:53,099
I'm not asking you right now.

278
00:23:53,099 --> 00:23:58,000
Everything... it's all my daughter's fault that this happened.

279
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:00,660
No, it's me... it's all me...

280
00:24:00,660 --> 00:24:03,561
(Chihiro) That's why I don't have the right to say things like this.

281
00:24:03,561 --> 00:24:07,759
I think I fully understand Kondo-san's feelings.

282
00:24:07,759 --> 00:24:13,165
But today is Mr. Osako's funeral.

283
00:24:13,165 --> 00:24:15,825
Shouldn't we quietly remember the deceased?

284
00:24:15,825 --> 00:24:19,330
(Sakura) Are you lying?

285
00:24:19,330 --> 00:24:24,660
Is that really it? I wanted to pay the settlement fee and get things settled.

286
00:24:24,660 --> 00:24:26,330
Otherwise it's work

287
00:24:26,330 --> 00:24:29,957
Because it would cause trouble for my current family other than Taro.

288
00:24:29,957 --> 00:24:31,924
So to wrap up that person

289
00:24:31,924 --> 00:24:33,726
You just came here to get in a good mood, right?

290
00:24:33,726 --> 00:24:35,396
(Chihiro) That can't be true, right?

291
00:24:35,396 --> 00:24:38,495
(Sae) Which one is the worst?

292
00:24:38,495 --> 00:24:41,066
That's what happened at my house all of a sudden.

293
00:24:41,066 --> 00:24:42,726
Bring me that settlement letter.

294
00:24:42,726 --> 00:24:45,297
My mom is also the worst, right?

295
00:24:45,297 --> 00:24:47,726
So I apologized for that, but...

296
00:24:47,726 --> 00:24:49,429
(Sae) Why is mom the worst? (Chihiro) Now

297
00:24:49,429 --> 00:24:51,099
Money can only be the solution, right?

298
00:24:51,099 --> 00:24:54,363
It's normal to look for the culprit at a funeral.

299
00:24:54,363 --> 00:24:56,462
(Chihiro) As the young lady says, who is the worst?

300
00:24:56,462 --> 00:25:01,660
Even if we look for the culprit... there's a different culprit, my daughter.

301
00:25:01,660 --> 00:25:03,495
That's not true!

302
00:25:05,561 --> 00:25:11,726
At that time, I was scared... I was scared that my affair would be found out.

303
00:25:11,726 --> 00:25:14,000
That's why I told you to run away...

304
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:17,033
That's not what I'm saying now.

305
00:25:17,033 --> 00:25:20,231
What do you mean by covering?

306
00:25:20,231 --> 00:25:23,561
This person senior

307
00:25:23,561 --> 00:25:25,396
Huh? Huh?

308
00:25:25,396 --> 00:25:30,561
So that day, I said I wanted a divorce, but I said no.

309
00:25:30,561 --> 00:25:32,594
Why don't you always listen to me?

310
00:25:32,594 --> 00:25:34,561
(Hiroshi) What's the difference? That's why I want a divorce...

311
00:25:34,561 --> 00:25:37,297
(Sae) A story from the past! The reason I wanted a divorce

312
00:25:37,297 --> 00:25:40,627
I've heard many times that it's not like that... (Sakura) I wonder if it used to be that way.

313
00:25:40,627 --> 00:25:47,033
♬〜

314
00:25:47,033 --> 00:25:52,099
Well, at least... what's the reason?

315
00:25:52,099 --> 00:25:54,297
Huh? (Sae) Reason

316
00:25:56,033 --> 00:25:58,000
Hey! Because write a will

317
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:01,726
Isn't it worth it to go up to the roof with that?

318
00:26:01,726 --> 00:26:04,858
So what is it? Did you have debt?

319
00:26:04,858 --> 00:26:07,198
Were you mentally ill? Were you sick?

320
00:26:07,198 --> 00:26:10,462
Yes, there is usually a reason.

321
00:26:10,462 --> 00:26:14,066
Or, after all, my daughter canceled my order suddenly.

322
00:26:14,066 --> 00:26:17,330
I was so shocked...

323
00:26:17,330 --> 00:26:22,396
Otherwise, will the mother die and leave her child behind?

324
00:26:22,396 --> 00:26:26,660
(Endo) That's... I don't think that's true.

325
00:26:29,891 --> 00:26:32,726
I can't generalize...

326
00:26:34,099 --> 00:26:36,759
(Sae) Why did anyone do it in the first place?

327
00:26:36,759 --> 00:26:38,594
Aren't you going to get arrested?

328
00:26:38,594 --> 00:26:41,594
This can only be described as an unexpected accident.

329
00:26:41,594 --> 00:26:44,297
(Sae) Who was the worst police officer?

330
00:26:44,297 --> 00:26:46,627
Because you can't decide properly!

331
00:26:46,627 --> 00:26:50,594
Even I don't want to do something so insane.

332
00:26:50,594 --> 00:26:54,462
But the person who is important to me...what is important to me?

333
00:26:54,462 --> 00:26:58,066
(Sae) Actually, you are the one who regrets it the most, right?

334
00:26:58,066 --> 00:27:00,000
Then, not me, but these people...

335
00:27:00,000 --> 00:27:01,660
Me!

336
00:27:01,660 --> 00:27:08,561
♬〜

337
00:27:08,561 --> 00:27:11,891
(Chihiro) I'm going home

338
00:27:11,891 --> 00:27:16,726
I'm really sorry for everything.

339
00:27:19,957 --> 00:27:24,792
(Sakura) Hehehehehe something?

340
00:27:25,792 --> 00:27:30,858
Taro: I'm glad I don't look like my aunt.

341
00:27:30,858 --> 00:27:33,891
Huh? that! It's really me...

342
00:27:33,891 --> 00:27:37,066
It was all me... I'm sorry!

343
00:27:37,066 --> 00:27:39,594
(Sae) Please don't disturb me now. I'm really... I'm really sorry!

344
00:27:39,594 --> 00:27:41,627
(Sae) Please be careful, no, it's me.

345
00:27:41,627 --> 00:27:45,033
(Sae) Please come back! Please come back!

346
00:27:53,198 --> 00:27:54,858
(Taro) Sister?

347
00:27:58,891 --> 00:28:01,198
It's good after all

348
00:28:02,924 --> 00:28:07,396
go home let's go home

349
00:28:07,396 --> 00:28:10,363
No, because my mother too...

350
00:28:10,363 --> 00:28:14,759
Sakura and her parents all gathered at the funeral...

351
00:28:14,759 --> 00:28:17,198
It's definitely a shambles

352
00:28:19,198 --> 00:28:22,924
About that person... When I tried to help...

353
00:28:25,396 --> 00:28:28,594
Because I can't help you

354
00:28:35,099 --> 00:28:38,693
(Misato)《I guess it's possible to try to forgive.》

355
00:28:38,693 --> 00:28:43,627
《Even if I make a lot of mistakes, I'm not a bad person》

356
00:28:45,363 --> 00:28:49,363
⚟♬「Small sunset glow」

357
00:28:49,363 --> 00:29:08,825
⚟♬〜

358
00:29:08,825 --> 00:29:12,231
(Chihiro) Dad? Dad!

359
00:29:12,231 --> 00:29:20,165
⚟♬〜

360
00:29:20,165 --> 00:29:25,495
Everything... I wish it was a dream...

361
00:29:26,924 --> 00:29:29,099
Huh?

362
00:29:29,099 --> 00:29:36,891
I wish everything about my birth had been a dream.

363
00:29:36,891 --> 00:29:39,165
(Chihiro) Ambulance please.

364
00:29:39,165 --> 00:29:43,891
Yes, when I came back, my husband had collapsed...

365
00:29:46,858 --> 00:29:53,033
If it weren't for me... I'd be all wrong...

366
00:29:56,264 --> 00:30:01,000
I just wanted to help...

367
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:14,198
♬〜

368
00:30:14,198 --> 00:30:20,396
There's nothing wrong with that feeling

369
00:30:20,396 --> 00:30:32,231
♬〜

370
00:30:32,231 --> 00:30:33,891
Sister?

371
00:30:33,891 --> 00:30:39,363
♬〜

372
00:30:39,363 --> 00:30:43,858
(sob)

373
00:30:43,858 --> 00:30:49,000
♬〜

374
00:30:53,000 --> 00:30:55,297
(Sae) After all, it will be settled in court... (Chihiro) That's why...

375
00:30:55,297 --> 00:30:58,297
For some reason... for some reason...

376
00:30:58,297 --> 00:31:00,792
(Sae) Yes?

377
00:31:00,792 --> 00:31:06,132
I think I might have been your mother... now.

378
00:31:06,132 --> 00:31:08,396
What is it?

379
00:31:08,396 --> 00:31:12,297
Because of this, I wonder if my mother wanted to die.

380
00:31:12,297 --> 00:31:15,462
(Sae) Huh? I understand

381
00:31:15,462 --> 00:31:17,891
I shouldn't say that...

382
00:31:17,891 --> 00:31:21,099
Now, I guess that's not the case...

383
00:31:21,099 --> 00:31:22,759
but…

384
00:31:26,066 --> 00:31:33,132
I thought my mother wanted to die.

385
00:31:33,132 --> 00:31:35,792
I don't think it's a mistake

386
00:31:39,297 --> 00:31:43,627
what? Huh? What do you want to say?

387
00:31:43,627 --> 00:31:49,396
Would I be able to say the same thing if I were dead?

388
00:31:53,627 --> 00:31:56,363
(footsteps)

389
00:32:02,759 --> 00:32:09,132
I'm really... sorry.

390
00:32:17,693 --> 00:32:20,957
What I did exactly...

391
00:32:20,957 --> 00:32:25,330
So... Mom, I'm sorry.

392
00:32:25,330 --> 00:32:31,957
But I have to pay money and stop going to court.

393
00:32:31,957 --> 00:32:34,594
Can you please stop doing that?

394
00:32:34,594 --> 00:32:37,957
(Chihiro) That's because... I can't pretend it didn't happen.

395
00:32:39,495 --> 00:32:42,660
It's all wrong...

396
00:32:42,660 --> 00:32:49,330
Just run away like that because you can't take it back anyway...

397
00:32:49,330 --> 00:32:56,825
I tried to pretend it never happened, but that was my biggest mistake.

398
00:32:59,396 --> 00:33:02,660
(Chihiro) When you make a mistake, solve it with money or ignore it...

399
00:33:02,660 --> 00:33:07,759
Even if mom ignores me or doesn't want to see me...

400
00:33:07,759 --> 00:33:12,132
No...actually, I don't want to see it either.

401
00:33:12,132 --> 00:33:19,891
But still... I'm here, right?

402
00:33:28,132 --> 00:33:31,099
(Sae) Hey, Dad, we're not done talking yet.

403
00:33:31,099 --> 00:33:34,198
It's already over

404
00:33:34,198 --> 00:33:36,561
Huh?

405
00:33:36,561 --> 00:33:40,264
Endo-san yes

406
00:33:40,264 --> 00:33:44,825
I have a small request...

407
00:33:44,825 --> 00:33:46,495
Huh?

408
00:33:55,099 --> 00:33:58,891
Let's go!

409
00:34:04,891 --> 00:34:07,627
Huh? Wait... what?

410
00:34:07,627 --> 00:34:09,495
(Endo) Ah...wait!

411
00:34:09,495 --> 00:34:14,924
♬〜

412
00:34:14,924 --> 00:34:17,858
(Taro) Kenken?

413
00:34:17,858 --> 00:34:21,858
Go home, where's your mom? Huh?

414
00:34:21,858 --> 00:34:26,759
(Sakura) Lock the door, then this is here.

415
00:34:26,759 --> 00:34:29,792
Put it in the mailbox at the end

416
00:34:33,363 --> 00:34:35,594
(Chihiro) Where are you going back?

417
00:34:40,231 --> 00:34:42,462
ourselves

418
00:34:45,495 --> 00:34:47,495
Ah so

419
00:34:47,495 --> 00:34:55,561
♬〜

420
00:34:55,561 --> 00:35:00,792
"I'm glad we don't look alike"... haha...

421
00:35:00,792 --> 00:35:20,792
♬〜

422
00:35:20,792 --> 00:35:25,594
♬〜

423
00:35:25,594 --> 00:35:29,132
(sigh)

424
00:35:29,132 --> 00:35:31,891
Please... it's okay.

425
00:35:31,891 --> 00:35:43,000
♬〜

426
00:36:01,495 --> 00:36:03,495
(sigh)

427
00:36:16,495 --> 00:36:20,462
Sorry last time?

428
00:36:20,462 --> 00:36:22,891
push me down the stairs

429
00:36:27,066 --> 00:36:29,759
Is your neck okay?

430
00:36:29,759 --> 00:36:35,726
Ah... it still hurts a little when I turn this way.

431
00:36:35,726 --> 00:36:40,000
I'm not facing you.

432
00:36:45,759 --> 00:36:50,297
Can I be honest? Huh?

433
00:36:50,297 --> 00:36:58,165
I don't think I'll ever be able to completely forgive you.

434
00:37:01,396 --> 00:37:03,066
Yeah…

435
00:37:05,891 --> 00:37:11,033
But... thank you

436
00:37:11,033 --> 00:37:12,693
Huh?

437
00:37:14,891 --> 00:37:20,231
Thank you for being by my mother's side at the very end.

438
00:37:25,891 --> 00:37:27,561
Yeah

439
00:37:33,066 --> 00:37:38,264
(Chihiro) Would you like to eat this? It's a waste

440
00:37:38,264 --> 00:37:50,693
♬〜

441
00:37:50,693 --> 00:37:54,957
(Chihiro) Unexpectedly, when we met normally,

442
00:37:54,957 --> 00:37:59,858
It seems so nice that we might become mom friends or something.

443
00:37:59,858 --> 00:38:04,198
Haha... At this age, you can call me a mom friend.

444
00:38:04,198 --> 00:38:09,825
Ordinary friends? What do you think?

445
00:38:11,165 --> 00:38:16,528
He seems to be talking a bit noisy, so I might not get along well with him.

446
00:38:16,528 --> 00:38:20,627
So, are you on the other side? good friends

447
00:38:24,165 --> 00:38:32,792
I... am I saying something that wrong?

448
00:38:32,792 --> 00:38:52,858
♬〜

449
00:38:52,858 --> 00:38:54,528
that!

450
00:38:56,231 --> 00:39:00,363
(breathing heavily)

451
00:39:02,066 --> 00:39:04,066
this…

452
00:39:04,066 --> 00:39:24,066
♬〜

453
00:39:24,066 --> 00:39:29,792
♬〜

454
00:39:29,792 --> 00:39:34,462
Ah!

455
00:39:34,462 --> 00:39:43,264
(breathing heavily)

456
00:39:43,264 --> 00:40:01,231
♬〜

457
00:40:01,231 --> 00:40:05,231
What should we do? You from now on

458
00:40:05,231 --> 00:40:07,957
What about that?

459
00:40:07,957 --> 00:40:13,693
I... aren't we the same?

460
00:40:13,693 --> 00:40:16,495
Even though I'm as irritated as ever

461
00:40:16,495 --> 00:40:18,924
Don't make a mistake

462
00:40:18,924 --> 00:40:22,528
Careful and jumpy

463
00:40:22,528 --> 00:40:28,099
And then I put up with it again and got irritated... It goes back and forth.

464
00:40:30,594 --> 00:40:34,495
But I guess that's not bad either.

465
00:40:34,495 --> 00:40:37,363
Huh?

466
00:40:37,363 --> 00:40:44,396
No, no, it's bad, I didn't do anything bad at all.

467
00:40:44,396 --> 00:40:49,198
I haven't done it, but I guess that's the way it is.

468
00:40:49,198 --> 00:40:51,198
Yeah…

469
00:40:53,033 --> 00:41:00,165
Because the world is full of landmines

470
00:41:00,165 --> 00:41:03,528
Things that I don't understand happen.

471
00:41:03,528 --> 00:41:06,429
No matter how seriously I live my life

472
00:41:06,429 --> 00:41:09,528
Huh? Something like this usually happens

473
00:41:09,528 --> 00:41:12,792
Huh? People like that are common too.

474
00:41:14,132 --> 00:41:17,297
I get irritated by that kind of thing

475
00:41:17,297 --> 00:41:21,000
But sometimes I'm happy...

476
00:41:23,825 --> 00:41:27,297
But I made a mistake again...

477
00:41:27,297 --> 00:41:32,957
Even if I try to be courageous, it's a mistake in itself

478
00:41:32,957 --> 00:41:36,792
I'm scared of making a mistake and I'm nervous

479
00:41:36,792 --> 00:41:40,429
I thought it was me who wasn't impressed.

480
00:41:40,429 --> 00:41:43,495
No, that's actually normal.

481
00:41:45,957 --> 00:41:52,330
If you can't feel anything, is that an error?

482
00:41:55,363 --> 00:42:01,231
Frustrated, scared, angry...

483
00:42:01,231 --> 00:42:07,495
I can't forgive it, I hate it...

484
00:42:07,495 --> 00:42:13,660
Cry, laugh...

485
00:42:13,660 --> 00:42:16,363
I was scared and ran away...

486
00:42:16,363 --> 00:42:23,528
Sometimes I want to die because I can't do it

487
00:42:23,528 --> 00:42:29,165
That's because I live a normal life.

488
00:42:29,165 --> 00:42:45,957
♬〜

489
00:42:45,957 --> 00:42:49,495
I wish we could have met in a different way.

490
00:42:49,495 --> 00:43:09,495
♬〜

491
00:43:09,495 --> 00:43:29,495
♬〜

492
00:43:29,495 --> 00:43:49,495
♬〜

493
00:43:49,495 --> 00:43:53,132
♬〜

494
00:43:53,132 --> 00:43:55,132
good morning

495
00:43:55,132 --> 00:44:01,858
♬〜

496
00:44:01,858 --> 00:44:03,858
good morning

497
00:44:03,858 --> 00:44:20,000
♬〜
